			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">VERY wrong in your definition of "tanking" here. Tanking is not so single faceted as you try to claim. Tanking is not the ability to take physical damage, it is the ability to MITIGATE the damage a mob does WHILE keeping it focused on attacking ONLY YOU!!!</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Nice try, but no. 
<br />

<br />
Pre nerf of tipt/vxed and up. 
<br />
A pally/SK can hold agro no problem for at least a good 10 minutes on any names there providing they didnn't die. 
<br />

<br />
The problem is that they do die because they are taking too much damage. 
<br />
And hence they were saying, "a war is needed to tank those trials". 
<br />

<br />
And duh, mitigate damage is part of taking how many damage. 
<br />
I.E. it's like me saying earth pet can tank mob XXX for time YYY and that is earth pet can take damage from mob XXX for time YYY. 
<br />

<br />
While you go, "NONONO, it's earth pet's ability ot mitigate damage too!!"
<br />

<br />
The ability to mitigate damage is in the equation of how much damage is taken. 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Maerlin wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Mitigating the damage can be done any number of ways and be considered equal. For example: 
<br />

<br />
Warriors mitigate damage through taking less damage per hit (DI-1) and through higher hit points as well as higher AC (in general). 
<br />

<br />
Paladin's (previously) mitigated damage through chain stunning (stuns aren't only used for aggro, some did used to actually land), as well as high AC, self healing ability, and high HP totals. 
<br />

<br />
SKs mitigate damage through various taps (debuff, lifetaps, etc) as well as high AC and high HP totals. 
<br />

<br />
ALL three options are considered "tanking", and should be balanced equally. For example... </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Let me put it to you once again. 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">A pally/SK can hold agro no problem for at least a good 10 minutes on any names there providing they didnn't die. 
<br />

<br />
The problem is that they do die because they are taking too much damage. 
<br />
And hence they were saying, "a war is needed to tank those trials". 
<br />

<br />
The ability to mitigate damage is in the equation of how much damage is taken. </span>
