			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In EQ, the terms Mitigation and Avoidance are separate and distinct.
<br />

<br />
Mitigation is the ability to NOT take the full amount of the blow that is incoming.
<br />

<br />
Avoidance is the ability to completely avoid the incoming blow.
<br />

<br />
That's why monks don't make great tanks in high damage scenarios since they mitigate like crap and avoid well.  they take "spike" damage and make healing more unpredictable.
<br />

<br />
Your point is well taken though.  However, the problem is that given the current content, mitigation is stronger due to the more predictable amount of healing needed against the mobs.  Once you start healing in these things you don't stop.  YOu can't because of the damage output.  Therefore, the person taking 1000 damage per hit on average Vs the person who gets a whiff then takes 2000 points of damage on hits is prefered over the later.
<br />

<br />
I do think that stuns should work on higher level mobs and that your hypothesis in the end about taking the same damage over time using different methods is good.  In order to do that then content really needs to be reworked and that is happening.  Additionally, tweaks to all classes need to occur for the balance to still happen.
<br />

<br />
To the original poster about us being balanced.  Sorry we aren't and I think everyone here has laid out why.<br />_________________<br />Sage Sarridon Soulcraver
<br />
Arch Convoker-Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
